This final was reconciled against the REAL repository (verified by reading migrations/0002_crm.sql, src/crm.js, src/worker.js, wrangler.toml, and docs/admin/index.html), not the layout the original attempts assumed. Ground truth that shaped the merge:
- `contacts` already exists (0002_crm.sql), co-owned with the CRM: columns id, name, phone, email, tags (CSV string), stage, notes, next_followup, consent_sms, consent_email, source, created. There is NO `updated` column and tags is CSV, not JSON.
- `normPhone()` is exported from src/crm.js and reused here (one E.164 definition).
- crm.js uses `env.DB` directly; there is currently NO `[[d1_databases]]` block in wrangler.toml, so this section adds it (the DB is shared by both).
- worker.js dispatches sub-routers INSIDE the gated `if (path.startsWith("/api/admin/"))` block. `handleCrm()` returns a Response for every path (including its own 404), so its dispatch is an unconditional `return handleCrm(...)` at line 108. This section's `handleAdminMarketing()` instead returns `null` for non-marketing admin paths, so its dispatch uses an `if (res) return res;` fall-through — matched exactly in the integration notes below.
- The admin panel is docs/admin/index.html; assets `directory = "docs"`; `run_worker_first = ["/api/*"]` (so `/u/*` must be added). The tabs handler already includes a CRM tab: the real array is `["leads", "crm", "listings", "copy"]` (line 164), and full contact create/edit already lives in that CRM tab — so the marketing Contacts tab is read + consent/tags-toggle only.

Base taken from the stronger attempt (SQL NOT EXISTS suppression anti-join instead of a per-contact isSuppressed loop; correct Twilio HMAC-SHA1+base64 inbound webhook; transient 429/5xx re-queue instead of permanent failure; self-contained /u/:token page; expiring signed unsub token). Grafted from the other attempt: recipient_count returned on campaign creation. Fixed in both: the wrong tabs array, the handleCrm-returns-a-Response integration detail, and the missing wrangler [[d1_databases]] block.

=== FILE: migrations/0001_marketing.sql ===
-- Marketing backend schema for adriancortez (D1 binding: DB).
-- Ordering note: 0002_crm.sql ALSO declares `contacts` with CREATE TABLE IF NOT
-- EXISTS and the SAME columns (its header comment says "0001 (marketing) creates
-- contacts"), so whichever migration runs first wins and the other's contacts
-- block is a harmless no-op. This file is the canonical owner of `contacts`.
-- Marketing OWNS: campaigns, sends, suppressions + additive indexes.
-- Idempotent: safe to re-run. No destructive statements.
--
-- Apply:  wrangler d1 migrations apply adriancortez-marketing            (remote)
--         wrangler d1 migrations apply adriancortez-marketing --local   (local dev)

-- ---------- contacts (shared with CRM; IDENTICAL shape to 0002_crm.sql) ----------
-- Column set, order, types, and defaults match 0002_crm.sql exactly so the two
-- migrations are order-independent. tags is a CSV string; created is ISO-8601;
-- there is NO `updated` column. Do NOT diverge this from 0002_crm.sql.
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS contacts (
  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  name          TEXT NOT NULL,
  phone         TEXT DEFAULT '',           -- E.164 (+1XXXXXXXXXX) or ''
  email         TEXT DEFAULT '',           -- lowercased or ''
  tags          TEXT DEFAULT '',           -- CSV string, e.g. "buyer,brickell,vip"
  stage         TEXT DEFAULT 'lead',
  notes         TEXT DEFAULT '',
  next_followup TEXT DEFAULT '',
  consent_sms   INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  consent_email INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  source        TEXT DEFAULT 'manual',
  created       TEXT NOT NULL
);
-- Marketing lookups: resolve a contact by address at STOP / unsubscribe time.
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_contacts_phone ON contacts(phone);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_contacts_email ON contacts(email);

-- ---------- campaigns (one row per SMS or email blast) ----------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS campaigns (
  id           TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  channel      TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (channel IN ('sms','email')),
  name         TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  subject      TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',     -- email only; ignored for sms
  body         TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',     -- supports {{name}} merge
  tag_filter   TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',     -- CSV of tags; '' = everyone consenting on channel
  status       TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'draft'
                 CHECK (status IN ('draft','scheduled','sending','sent','paused')),
  scheduled_at TEXT,                          -- ISO-8601 UTC; NULL for send-now
  created      TEXT NOT NULL
);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_campaigns_status ON campaigns(status);
-- The cron scans due, sendable campaigns on this composite.
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_campaigns_due ON campaigns(status, scheduled_at);

-- ---------- sends (one row per recipient per campaign) ----------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS sends (
  id          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  campaign_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  contact_id  TEXT NOT NULL,
  channel     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (channel IN ('sms','email')),
  address     TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',      -- resolved phone/email at enqueue time
  status      TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued'
                CHECK (status IN ('queued','sent','delivered','failed','suppressed')),
  provider_id TEXT DEFAULT '',               -- Twilio SID / Resend id
  error       TEXT DEFAULT '',
  ts          TEXT NOT NULL                  -- last-updated ISO-8601
);
-- Guard against double-enqueueing the same contact in the same campaign
-- (makes INSERT OR IGNORE a true idempotent upsert on re-enqueue).
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS ux_sends_camp_contact ON sends(campaign_id, contact_id);
-- The cron pulls the next queued chunk on this composite.
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_sends_queue ON sends(campaign_id, status);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_sends_status ON sends(status);

-- ---------- suppressions (global do-not-contact per channel) ----------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS suppressions (
  id      TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  value   TEXT NOT NULL,                     -- phone (E.164) or lowercased email
  channel TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (channel IN ('sms','email')),
  reason  TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',          -- stop|unsubscribe|help|manual|bounce|complaint
  ts      TEXT NOT NULL
);
-- value+channel is the lookup key; unique so re-suppression is a no-op upsert.
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS ux_suppress_value_chan ON suppressions(value, channel);
=== END FILE ===

=== FILE: src/marketing.js ===
// Marketing backend for the adriancortez worker: marketing contact views,
// campaigns CRUD, CSV / lead-inbox import, the send-queue state machine, quiet
// hours + consent + suppression gates, the Twilio inbound webhook (STOP/HELP/
// START), the signed unsubscribe page (/u/:token), and the cron tick that moves
// scheduled -> sending and drains the queue in bounded chunks.
//
// SHARES the `contacts` table with src/crm.js. It reuses that module's exported
// normPhone() so E.164 normalization is defined in ONE place, and it treats
// `tags` as a CSV string (the shape crm.js and the CRM UI already use) — NOT a
// JSON array. There is NO `updated` column on contacts in this codebase.
//
// Wiring: src/worker.js imports { handleMarketing, handleAdminMarketing, runCron }:
//   - handleMarketing(req, env, url) handles the PUBLIC routes (/u/:token and
//     /api/hooks/twilio) and returns a Response, or null to fall through. It is
//     dispatched BEFORE the /api/admin/ block so the admin gate never 401s them.
//   - handleAdminMarketing(req, env, url) handles /api/admin/marketing/* and is
//     dispatched INSIDE the already-gated /api/admin/ block (so it does NOT
//     re-check isAdmin). It returns a Response for a marketing route, or null so
//     the block's own 404 still fires. NOTE: unlike crm.js's handleCrm (which
//     returns a Response for EVERY path, hence an unconditional `return`), this
//     one returns null on miss, so worker.js dispatches it as `if (res) return res;`.
//   - runCron(env) is called from the exported scheduled() handler.
//
// Provider transports (Twilio SMS / Resend email) run in safe DEMO MODE when
// their secrets are absent: they record a synthetic provider id instead of
// calling out, so the whole contacts -> campaign -> queue -> cron pipeline is
// testable before Twilio/Resend accounts are live. The moment the secrets exist,
// real sends happen with no code change.
//
// A2P 10DLC: sending marketing SMS to US numbers requires a registered 10DLC
// brand + campaign in the Twilio console. That is an account-level prerequisite,
// not code.

import { normPhone } from "./crm.js";

// ============================================================================
// shared helpers (mirror worker.js / crm.js conventions)
// ============================================================================

const json = (data, status = 200, headers = {}) =>
  new Response(JSON.stringify(data), {
    status,
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json", "Cache-Control": "no-store", ...headers },
  });

// HMAC-SHA256 -> lowercase hex. Matches worker.js's hmac() (used for unsub token).
async function hmac(secret, msg) {
  const key = await crypto.subtle.importKey(
    "raw", new TextEncoder().encode(secret), { name: "HMAC", hash: "SHA-256" }, false, ["sign"]
  );
  const sig = await crypto.subtle.sign("HMAC", key, new TextEncoder().encode(msg));
  return [...new Uint8Array(sig)].map((b) => b.toString(16).padStart(2, "0")).join("");
}

// HMAC-SHA1 -> base64. Required ONLY for Twilio's webhook signature (Twilio
// signs with HMAC-SHA1 and base64s the raw digest — NOT SHA-256).
async function hmacSha1B64(secret, msg) {
  const key = await crypto.subtle.importKey(
    "raw", new TextEncoder().encode(secret), { name: "HMAC", hash: "SHA-1" }, false, ["sign"]
  );
  const sig = await crypto.subtle.sign("HMAC", key, new TextEncoder().encode(msg));
  return btoa(String.fromCharCode(...new Uint8Array(sig)));
}

const clean = (v, max = 500) => String(v ?? "").trim().slice(0, max);
const uuid = () => crypto.randomUUID();
const nowIso = () => new Date().toISOString();

// Constant-time-ish string compare (token / signature verification).
function safeEqual(a, b) {
  if (typeof a !== "string" || typeof b !== "string") return false;
  if (a.length !== b.length) return false;
  let diff = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < a.length; i++) diff |= a.charCodeAt(i) ^ b.charCodeAt(i);
  return diff === 0;
}

async function parseBody(req) {
  try { return await req.json(); } catch { return null; }
}

const EMAIL_RE = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]{2,}$/;
function normEmail(raw) {
  const s = clean(raw, 160).toLowerCase();
  return EMAIL_RE.test(s) ? s : "";
}

// Normalize a CSV tag string to a clean, de-duped, lowercased array.
function tagList(csv) {
  return [...new Set(
    String(csv ?? "").split(",").map((t) => t.trim().toLowerCase()).filter(Boolean)
  )];
}
function tagsToCsv(input) {
  const arr = Array.isArray(input) ? input : String(input ?? "").split(",");
  return [...new Set(arr.map((t) => clean(t, 40).toLowerCase()).filter(Boolean))].slice(0, 40).join(",");
}

// {{name}} merge — SMS/email bodies are plain text (email HTML is escaped later),
// so no escaping needed at merge time. Falls back to a friendly default.
function mergeBody(body, contact) {
  const name = clean(contact?.name, 80) || "there";
  return String(body ?? "").replace(/\{\{\s*name\s*\}\}/gi, name);
}

// ============================================================================
// compliance: quiet hours + STOP notice
// ============================================================================

// Local wall-clock hour (0..23) in America/New_York, DST-correct via Intl.
function nyHour(ts = Date.now()) {
  const parts = new Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-US", {
    timeZone: "America/New_York", hour: "2-digit", hour12: false,
  }).formatToParts(new Date(ts));
  const h = Number(parts.find((p) => p.type === "hour")?.value ?? "12");
  return h === 24 ? 0 : h;
}
const SMS_START_HOUR = 9;  // inclusive
const SMS_END_HOUR = 20;   // exclusive (last send 19:59 ET)
function smsWithinQuietHours(ts = Date.now()) {
  const h = nyHour(ts);
  return h >= SMS_START_HOUR && h < SMS_END_HOUR;
}

// Marketing SMS must carry an opt-out. Append if missing (case-insensitive,
// idempotent — bodies that already say STOP aren't double-footered).
const STOP_NOTICE = "Txt STOP to opt out";
function withStopNotice(body) {
  const b = String(body ?? "");
  if (/\bstop\b/i.test(b)) return b;
  return (b.trimEnd() + (b.trim() ? " " : "") + STOP_NOTICE);
}

// ============================================================================
// signed unsubscribe token (email one-click)
// ============================================================================
// Token = base64url(value|channel|exp) . HMAC-SHA256(secret, "unsub:"+payload).
// Baked-in expiry so a leaked link can't unsubscribe someone forever. Signed
// with UNSUB_SECRET if set, else the existing ADMIN_KEY (no new required secret).

const UNSUB_TTL_MS = 180 * 24 * 3600 * 1000; // 180 days

function b64urlEncode(s) {
  return btoa(s).replace(/\+/g, "-").replace(/\//g, "_").replace(/=+$/, "");
}
function b64urlDecode(s) {
  const pad = s.length % 4 ? "=".repeat(4 - (s.length % 4)) : "";
  return atob(s.replace(/-/g, "+").replace(/_/g, "/") + pad);
}
function unsubSecret(env) {
  return env.UNSUB_SECRET || env.ADMIN_KEY;
}
async function signUnsub(env, value, channel) {
  const payload = `${value}|${channel}|${Date.now() + UNSUB_TTL_MS}`;
  const sig = await hmac(unsubSecret(env), `unsub:${payload}`);
  return `${b64urlEncode(payload)}.${sig}`;
}
async function verifyUnsub(env, token) {
  try {
    const dot = token.lastIndexOf(".");
    if (dot < 0) return null;
    const enc = token.slice(0, dot);
    const sig = token.slice(dot + 1);
    const payload = b64urlDecode(enc);
    const expected = await hmac(unsubSecret(env), `unsub:${payload}`);
    if (!safeEqual(sig, expected)) return null;
    const [value, channel, expStr] = payload.split("|");
    if (!value || !channel) return null;
    if (Number(expStr) && Number(expStr) < Date.now()) return null; // expired
    return { value, channel };
  } catch { return null; }
}

// ============================================================================
// DB access layer
// ============================================================================

function db(env) {
  if (!env.DB) throw new Error("DB binding missing (D1 not configured)");
  return env.DB;
}

async function getContact(env, id) {
  return db(env).prepare("SELECT * FROM contacts WHERE id = ?").bind(id).first();
}

async function isSuppressed(env, value, channel) {
  if (!value) return true;
  const r = await db(env).prepare(
    "SELECT 1 FROM suppressions WHERE value = ? AND channel = ? LIMIT 1"
  ).bind(value, channel).first();
  return !!r;
}

async function addSuppression(env, value, channel, reason) {
  if (!value) return;
  await db(env).prepare(
    `INSERT INTO suppressions (id,value,channel,reason,ts) VALUES (?,?,?,?,?)
     ON CONFLICT(value,channel) DO UPDATE SET reason=excluded.reason, ts=excluded.ts`
  ).bind(uuid(), value, channel, clean(reason, 40) || "manual", nowIso()).run();
}

async function removeSuppression(env, value, channel) {
  // NOTE: removing a suppression row does NOT re-grant consent. Re-opt-in is a
  // separate explicit action (inbound START, or an admin toggling consent).
  await db(env).prepare("DELETE FROM suppressions WHERE value = ? AND channel = ?")
    .bind(value, channel).run();
}

// ============================================================================
// segmentation / recipient resolution — the SINGLE source of truth
// ============================================================================
// Used by BOTH the live recipient counter (UI preview) and the enqueue step,
// so the confirmed count equals exactly who gets messaged. Consent is enforced
// in SQL; suppression is enforced with a NOT EXISTS anti-join (no per-contact
// query) so resolving/counting a 500-contact list is ONE subrequest, not 500.
//
// Tags are CSV. To match a tag EXACTLY (so "buy" doesn't match "buyer") without
// json_each (the column is a plain CSV string, not a JSON array), pad both sides
// with commas: instr(','||lower(tags)||',', ',tag,') > 0.

function recipientQuery(channel, tagFilter) {
  const addrCol = channel === "sms" ? "phone" : "email";
  const consentCol = channel === "sms" ? "consent_sms" : "consent_email";
  const tags = tagList(tagFilter);
  let sql =
    `SELECT c.* FROM contacts c
      WHERE c.${consentCol} = 1
        AND c.${addrCol} IS NOT NULL AND c.${addrCol} <> ''
        AND NOT EXISTS (
          SELECT 1 FROM suppressions s
           WHERE s.value = c.${addrCol} AND s.channel = ?
        )`;
  const binds = [channel];
  for (const t of tags) {
    // AND semantics: contact must carry every tag in the filter.
    sql += ` AND instr(',' || lower(c.tags) || ',', ?) > 0`;
    binds.push(`,${t},`);
  }
  return { sql, binds, addrCol };
}

async function resolveRecipients(env, channel, tagFilter) {
  const { sql, binds } = recipientQuery(channel, tagFilter);
  const { results } = await db(env).prepare(sql).bind(...binds).all();
  return results || [];
}

async function countRecipients(env, channel, tagFilter) {
  const { sql, binds } = recipientQuery(channel, tagFilter);
  const countSql = `SELECT COUNT(*) AS n FROM (${sql})`;
  const row = await db(env).prepare(countSql).bind(...binds).first();
  return row?.n ?? 0;
}

// ============================================================================
// provider transports (Twilio SMS / Resend email) — demo mode when unconfigured
// ============================================================================
// Each returns { ok, id?, error?, demo?, retryable? }. Compliance transforms
// (STOP notice, unsubscribe footer) are applied by the CALLER before these run,
// so transports stay dumb. retryable=true on 429/5xx and network errors.

async function sendSmsMessage(env, to, body) {
  if (!env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID || !env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN || !env.TWILIO_FROM) {
    return { ok: true, id: `demo-sms-${uuid().slice(0, 8)}`, demo: true };
  }
  const url = `https://api.twilio.com/2010-04-01/Accounts/${env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID}/Messages.json`;
  const auth = btoa(`${env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID}:${env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN}`);
  const form = new URLSearchParams({ To: to, From: env.TWILIO_FROM, Body: body });
  try {
    const r = await fetch(url, {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { Authorization: `Basic ${auth}`, "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" },
      body: form,
    });
    const data = await r.json().catch(() => ({}));
    if (!r.ok) return { ok: false, error: clean(data.message || `twilio ${r.status}`, 200), retryable: r.status === 429 || r.status >= 500 };
    return { ok: true, id: data.sid || "" };
  } catch (e) {
    return { ok: false, error: String(e).slice(0, 200), retryable: true };
  }
}

async function sendEmailMessage(env, to, subject, textBody, unsubUrl) {
  if (!env.RESEND_API_KEY || !env.EMAIL_FROM) {
    return { ok: true, id: `demo-email-${uuid().slice(0, 8)}`, demo: true };
  }
  const escHtml = (s) => String(s).replace(/[&<>]/g, (c) => ({ "&": "&amp;", "<": "&lt;", ">": "&gt;" }[c]));
  const html =
    `${escHtml(textBody).replace(/\n/g, "<br>")}` +
    `<br><br><hr><small><a href="${unsubUrl}">Unsubscribe</a></small>`;
  const text = `${textBody}\n\n---\nUnsubscribe: ${unsubUrl}`;
  try {
    const r = await fetch("https://api.resend.com/emails", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${env.RESEND_API_KEY}`, "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        from: env.EMAIL_FROM,
        to: [to],
        subject,
        html,
        text,
        headers: {
          "List-Unsubscribe": `<${unsubUrl}>`,
          "List-Unsubscribe-Post": "List-Unsubscribe=One-Click",
        },
      }),
    });
    const data = await r.json().catch(() => ({}));
    if (!r.ok) return { ok: false, error: clean(data.message || `resend ${r.status}`, 200), retryable: r.status === 429 || r.status >= 500 };
    return { ok: true, id: data.id || "" };
  } catch (e) {
    return { ok: false, error: String(e).slice(0, 200), retryable: true };
  }
}

function publicBase(env) {
  return (env.PUBLIC_BASE_URL || "https://adriancortez.com").replace(/\/+$/, "");
}

// ============================================================================
// campaign send lifecycle
// ============================================================================

// Enqueue: one queued send row per resolved recipient. Idempotent via the
// UNIQUE(campaign_id, contact_id) index + INSERT OR IGNORE. Chunked batches of
// 100 keep each invocation within the Workers subrequest budget.
async function enqueueCampaign(env, campaign) {
  const recips = await resolveRecipients(env, campaign.channel, campaign.tag_filter);
  const t = nowIso();
  const stmt = db(env).prepare(
    `INSERT OR IGNORE INTO sends (id,campaign_id,contact_id,channel,address,status,ts)
     VALUES (?,?,?,?,?, 'queued', ?)`
  );
  let batch = [];
  for (const c of recips) {
    const addr = campaign.channel === "sms" ? c.phone : c.email;
    batch.push(stmt.bind(uuid(), campaign.id, c.id, campaign.channel, addr, t));
    if (batch.length >= 100) { await db(env).batch(batch); batch = []; }
  }
  if (batch.length) await db(env).batch(batch);
  return recips.length;
}

// Process up to `limit` queued sends across actively-sending campaigns.
// Re-checks consent + suppression AT SEND TIME (a contact may opt out between
// enqueue and send). SMS quiet hours enforced per row. Transient provider
// failures (429/5xx/network) stay 'queued' for a later tick; hard failures
// are marked 'failed'.
async function processQueue(env, limit = 50) {
  const smsAllowed = smsWithinQuietHours();

  const { results: rows } = await db(env).prepare(
    `SELECT s.id AS send_id, s.contact_id, s.channel,
            c.body AS c_body, c.subject AS c_subject
       FROM sends s JOIN campaigns c ON c.id = s.campaign_id
      WHERE s.status = 'queued' AND c.status = 'sending'
      ORDER BY s.ts ASC LIMIT ?`
  ).bind(limit).all();

  let processed = 0;
  for (const s of rows || []) {
    // Quiet hours: leave SMS queued for a later in-window tick.
    if (s.channel === "sms" && !smsAllowed) continue;

    const contact = await getContact(env, s.contact_id);
    if (!contact) { await markSend(env, s.send_id, "failed", "", "contact deleted"); processed++; continue; }

    const addr = s.channel === "sms" ? contact.phone : contact.email;
    const consented = s.channel === "sms" ? contact.consent_sms : contact.consent_email;

    if (!addr || !consented || (await isSuppressed(env, addr, s.channel))) {
      await markSend(env, s.send_id, "suppressed", "", "no consent / suppressed at send time");
      processed++;
      continue;
    }

    let res;
    if (s.channel === "sms") {
      const body = withStopNotice(mergeBody(s.c_body, contact));
      res = await sendSmsMessage(env, addr, body);
    } else {
      const body = mergeBody(s.c_body, contact);
      const token = await signUnsub(env, addr, "email");
      const unsubUrl = `${publicBase(env)}/u/${token}`;
      res = await sendEmailMessage(env, addr, s.c_subject || "A note from Adrian Cortez", body, unsubUrl);
    }

    if (res.ok) {
      await markSend(env, s.send_id, "sent", res.id || "", "");
    } else if (res.retryable) {
      // transient — bump ts so it sorts to the back, retry next tick
      await db(env).prepare("UPDATE sends SET ts=?, error=? WHERE id=?")
        .bind(nowIso(), clean(res.error, 200), s.send_id).run();
    } else {
      await markSend(env, s.send_id, "failed", "", res.error || "send failed");
    }
    processed++;
  }
  return processed;
}

async function markSend(env, id, status, providerId, error) {
  await db(env).prepare(
    "UPDATE sends SET status=?, provider_id=?, error=?, ts=? WHERE id=?"
  ).bind(status, providerId || "", error ? clean(error, 300) : "", nowIso(), id).run();
}

// Flip fully-drained sending campaigns to 'sent'.
async function finalizeCampaigns(env) {
  const { results } = await db(env).prepare(
    "SELECT id FROM campaigns WHERE status = 'sending'"
  ).all();
  for (const c of results || []) {
    const rem = await db(env).prepare(
      "SELECT COUNT(*) AS n FROM sends WHERE campaign_id = ? AND status = 'queued'"
    ).bind(c.id).first();
    if (rem && rem.n === 0) {
      await db(env).prepare("UPDATE campaigns SET status='sent' WHERE id=?").bind(c.id).run();
    }
  }
}

// Live stats from sends (no denormalized counters to drift).
async function campaignStats(env, campaignId) {
  const { results } = await db(env).prepare(
    "SELECT status, COUNT(*) AS n FROM sends WHERE campaign_id = ? GROUP BY status"
  ).bind(campaignId).all();
  const out = { queued: 0, sent: 0, delivered: 0, failed: 0, suppressed: 0 };
  for (const r of results || []) out[r.status] = r.n;
  out.total = Object.values(out).reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
  return out;
}

// ============================================================================
// cron entry point — scheduled -> sending -> drain -> finalize
// ============================================================================
async function runCron(env) {
  if (!env.DB) return { skipped: "no DB" };
  const t = nowIso();

  // 1) scheduled -> sending for anything now due + enqueue its recipients.
  const { results: due } = await db(env).prepare(
    "SELECT * FROM campaigns WHERE status = 'scheduled' AND scheduled_at IS NOT NULL AND scheduled_at <= ?"
  ).bind(t).all();
  for (const c of due || []) {
    // SMS scheduled outside the window stays 'scheduled' until a later tick.
    if (c.channel === "sms" && !smsWithinQuietHours()) continue;
    await db(env).prepare("UPDATE campaigns SET status='sending' WHERE id=?").bind(c.id).run();
    await enqueueCampaign(env, c);
  }

  // 2) drain queued sends in a bounded chunk (default 50/tick).
  const chunk = Number(env.SEND_CHUNK || 50);
  const processed = await processQueue(env, chunk);

  // 3) finalize drained campaigns.
  await finalizeCampaigns(env);

  return { due: (due || []).length, processed };
}

// ============================================================================
// Twilio inbound webhook — STOP / HELP / START (CTIA keywords)
// ============================================================================

// Validate X-Twilio-Signature per Twilio's spec: HMAC-SHA1(authToken, fullUrl +
// sorted(k+v for each POST param)), base64. Reads the body ONCE via formData().
async function handleTwilioWebhook(req, env, url) {
  if (!env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN) {
    // No token configured => cannot verify => refuse (fail closed).
    return new Response("not configured", { status: 503 });
  }
  let form;
  try { form = await req.formData(); } catch { return new Response("bad request", { status: 400 }); }

  const params = [...form.entries()].sort((a, b) => (a[0] < b[0] ? -1 : a[0] > b[0] ? 1 : 0));
  let toSign = url.toString();
  for (const [k, v] of params) toSign += k + v;
  const expected = await hmacSha1B64(env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN, toSign);
  const provided = req.headers.get("X-Twilio-Signature") || "";
  if (!safeEqual(provided, expected)) return new Response("forbidden", { status: 403 });

  const from = clean(form.get("From") || "", 20);
  const raw = clean(form.get("Body") || "", 160).trim().toUpperCase().replace(/[^A-Z]/g, "");

  const STOP = new Set(["STOP", "STOPALL", "UNSUBSCRIBE", "CANCEL", "END", "QUIT"]);
  const START = new Set(["START", "UNSTOP", "YES"]);
  const HELP = new Set(["HELP", "INFO"]);

  let reply = "";
  if (env.DB && from) {
    if (STOP.has(raw)) {
      await addSuppression(env, from, "sms", "stop");
      await db(env).prepare("UPDATE contacts SET consent_sms=0 WHERE phone=?").bind(from).run();
      reply = "You're unsubscribed from Adrian Cortez texts. Reply START to opt back in.";
    } else if (START.has(raw)) {
      await removeSuppression(env, from, "sms");
      await db(env).prepare("UPDATE contacts SET consent_sms=1 WHERE phone=?").bind(from).run();
      reply = "You're opted back in to Adrian Cortez texts. Reply STOP to opt out anytime.";
    } else if (HELP.has(raw)) {
      reply = "Adrian Cortez Real Estate. Reply STOP to opt out. Msg&data rates may apply.";
    }
  }

  const escXml = (s) => String(s).replace(/[&<>"']/g, (c) => ({ "&": "&amp;", "<": "&lt;", ">": "&gt;", '"': "&quot;", "'": "&apos;" }[c]));
  const twiml = reply
    ? `<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Response><Message>${escXml(reply)}</Message></Response>`
    : `<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Response></Response>`;
  return new Response(twiml, { headers: { "Content-Type": "text/xml" } });
}

// ============================================================================
// unsubscribe page — public GET /u/:token
// ============================================================================

async function handleUnsubscribe(env, token) {
  const parsed = await verifyUnsub(env, decodeURIComponent(token));
  if (!parsed) {
    return htmlPage("Link expired", "This unsubscribe link is invalid or has expired. If you're still getting emails, reply to one and Adrian will remove you.", false, 400);
  }
  const { value, channel } = parsed;
  if (env.DB) {
    await addSuppression(env, value, channel, "unsubscribe");
    if (channel === "email") {
      await db(env).prepare("UPDATE contacts SET consent_email=0 WHERE email=?").bind(value).run();
    } else {
      await db(env).prepare("UPDATE contacts SET consent_sms=0 WHERE phone=?").bind(value).run();
    }
  }
  return htmlPage("You're unsubscribed", `You've been removed from ${channel === "sms" ? "text" : "email"} marketing from Adrian Cortez. It may take a moment to take effect across pending messages.`, true, 200);
}

function htmlPage(title, msg, ok, status) {
  const accent = ok ? "#14594E" : "#B4483A";
  const body = `<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
<meta name="robots" content="noindex,nofollow">
<title>${title} — Adrian Cortez</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bodoni+Moda:opsz,wght@6..96,600..700&family=Archivo:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
body{font-family:"Archivo",sans-serif;display:grid;place-items:center;min-height:100vh;background:#FCFBF8;color:#0E141C;padding:1.5rem}
.card{max-width:440px;text-align:center}
