=== DESIGN NOTES / why these choices (grounded in the verified repo) ===
- REUSES the shared schema: contacts exists (0002_crm.sql) with tags as a CSV
  string and no `updated` column. 0001 declares contacts identically so order
  doesn't matter. normPhone() imported from crm.js (one E.164 definition). CSV
  tags matched with a comma-padded instr() so "buy" never matches "buyer",
  index-safe and with NO json_each (which throws on a non-JSON column).
- SINGLE source of truth: recipientQuery() backs BOTH the live counter and
  enqueue, so the confirmed count is the sent set. Suppression is a NOT EXISTS
  anti-join in SQL, so resolving/counting a 500-contact list is ONE subrequest
  (not a per-contact isSuppressed loop, which would risk the Workers subrequest
  cap). isSuppressed() remains only for the single-row at-send-time re-check.
- Compliance enforced at resolve, enqueue, AND send: SMS quiet hours 09:00-20:00
  America/New_York (DST-correct via Intl), STOP notice auto-appended idempotently,
  consent + suppression re-checked at the moment of send. SMS scheduled outside
  the window waits (checked in both runCron and processQueue).
- Correct Twilio inbound: HMAC-SHA1 + base64(raw digest) signature validation
  (SHA-256 would reject every real webhook), body read once via formData(),
  fail-closed (503) without the token. STOP/HELP/START per CTIA keyword sets.
- Signed unsubscribe tokens carry a 180-day expiry + constant-time verify;
  List-Unsubscribe + one-click POST headers on every email; /u/* added to
  run_worker_first so the page actually reaches the worker.
- Transient provider 429/5xx/network errors are re-queued for the next tick
  (ts bumped so they sort to the back), not permanently failed.
- Stats computed live from sends via GROUP BY (no denormalized counters to drift).
- Opting a contact back in (consent PATCH, or SMS START) clears the matching
  suppression — but removing a suppression row alone does NOT auto-re-grant
  consent (avoids the compliance footgun).
- Existing endpoints byte-identical: handleMarketing returns null for any
  non-public path; handleAdminMarketing returns null for non-marketing admin
  paths; so /api/lead, /api/content, /api/admin/leads, /api/admin/crm/* behavior
  is unchanged, and worker.js's admin-block 404 still fires for genuine misses.

