--- compliance / correctness notes (email) ---
- Suppression enforced TWICE: seedEmailQueue excludes suppressed/no-consent contacts at queue time; the
  cron send loop re-checks consent_email + suppressions immediately before each Resend call (closes the
  schedule->send race). Skipped recipients are recorded status='suppressed', never silently dropped.
- {{name}} is HTML-escaped into the HTML body (escHtml) and raw in the text body; subject/From are CR/LF-
  stripped (headerSafe); the To field is a bare address string — no header injection surface.
- List-Unsubscribe + List-Unsubscribe-Post:One-Click on every send; the one-click POST target is the SAME
  /u/:token URL advertised in List-Unsubscribe, so Gmail/Yahoo one-click (RFC 8058) works. Precedence:bulk set.
- Unsubscribe tokens are HMAC(ADMIN_KEY,"e|contactId|email"): un-forgeable, no DB storage, constant-time
  verified, never expire, and embed the email so /u still suppresses after a contact row is deleted.
- Sends are chunked at 45/tick (< Free-plan 50 external-subrequest ceiling), one campaign per invocation;
  send-now returns immediately (no ctx.waitUntil in this worker) and the queue drains over cron ticks.
- PUBLIC_ORIGIN is required: both send-now and the cron refuse to send when it is unset, guaranteeing every
  unsubscribe link resolves to the real domain (no CAN-SPAM-breaking placeholder links).
- Resend webhook auto-suppresses hard bounces + spam complaints with correct Svix signature verification
  (base64 sig over the base64-decoded whsec_ key, v1, prefix, constant-time compare).

